steps.instruction:
For a more step by step guide you can look [here](https://www.kingarthurflour.com/blog/2010/06/01/what-do-readers-say-about-our-gluten-free-pizza-crust-%E2%80%9Camazing%E2%80%9D)

### Mixing
1. Place the dry ingredients (other than the yeast, sugar or honey) in a large bowl
    - Or the bowl of your stand mixer
2. Place the sugar or honey, warm water, 2 tablespoons of olive oil, yeast and about 1/2 cup of the dry mixture into a small bowl. Stir to combine
    - A few clumps are fine, set aside for 30 minutes or so
3. Add the wet mixture to the dry mixture
4. Beat on medium high for 4 minutes
    - The mixture will be thick and sticky 
        - It apparently is exactly lick spackling compound for walls or something. Aim for that consistency
5. Cover the dough and let rest for 30 minutes or so

### Shaping and Baking
6. Preheat the over to 425F 
7. Drizzle 2 tablespoons of olive oil onto the center of a baking sheet or 12" round pizza pan
8. Put the dough onto the oil puddle
9. Using *wet* fingers, start at the center of the dough and work outwards, pressing into a 12" to 14" circle
10. Let the dough rest for 15 minutes
11. Bake the crust for 8 to 10 minutes, just until it's set
12. Add toppings
13. Put back into oven for 10 to 15 minutes to finish baking

#### Tips
- To bake your pizza on a baking stone
    - Place the stone on the center rack and preheat your oven to 425F
    - Drizzle 2 tablespoons of olive oil onto the center of a half sheet pf parchment paper (about 12"x16")
    - Scrape the dough from the bowl onto the oil and paper 
    - Using wet fingers press the dough into a 12" circle, starting in the center and working out
    - Let the dough rest uncovered for 15 minutes
    - Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, just until set
    - Remove from oven
    - Return to the oven for 10 to 15 more minutes
- Want to experiment with different cheeses beyond the standard mozzarella? Choose those that melt well: Fontina, cheddar, Jack, provolone, brick, Gouda, and Muenster are all good candidates.
